Introduced Version
SENATE BILL No. 157
_____
DIGEST OF INTRODUCED BILL
Citations Affected: IC 27-1-24.6.
Synopsis: Disclosures related to prescription drugs. Provides that a
health plan must provide the amount of the national average drug
acquisition cost for a generic drug on the written materials provided to
the covered individual at the point of sale of the generic drug.
Effective: July 1, 2026.
Bohacek
January 5, 2026, read first time and referred to Committee on Insurance and Financial
Institutions.
2026 IN 157—LS 6545/DI 154

Introduced
Second Regular Session of the 124th General Assembly (2026)
PRINTING CODE. Amendments: Whenever an existing statute (or a section of the Indiana
Constitution) is being amended, the text of the existing provision will appear in this style type,
additions will appear in this style type, and deletions will appear in this style type.
Additions: Whenever a new statutory provision is being enacted (or a new constitutional
provision adopted), the text of the new provision will appear in this style type. Also, the
word NEW will appear in that style type in the introductory clause of each SECTION that adds
a new provision to the Indiana Code or the Indiana Constitution.
Conflict reconciliation: Text in a statute in this style type or this style type reconciles conflicts
between statutes enacted by the 2025 Regular Session of the General Assembly.
SENATE BILL No. 157
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
insurance.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 27-1-24.6-1, AS ADDED BY P.L.216-2025,
2 SECTION 41, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) This chapter applies to generic drugs
4 covered under a health plan after December 31, 2025.
5 (b) The amendments made to this chapter in the 2026 session of
6 the general assembly apply to generic drugs covered under a health
7 plan after December 31, 2026.
8 SECTION 2. IC 27-1-24.6-1.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
9 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
10 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1.5. As used in this chapter,
11 "covered individual" means an individual who is entitled to
12 coverage under a health plan.
13 SECTION 3. IC 27-1-24.6-6, AS ADDED BY P.L.216-2025,
14 SECTION 41, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
15 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 6. A health plan must provide the amount of the
16 national average drug acquisition cost for a generic drug:
17 (1) to the plan sponsor; and
2026 IN 157—LS 6545/DI 154

2
1 (2) on the written materials provided to the covered individual
2 at the point of sale of the generic drug.
